</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A type <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is said to be <fr:em><fr:strong>contractible with centre <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a:A]]></fr:tex></fr:strong></fr:em> when every <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x:A]]></fr:tex> is equipped with an identification <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\chi _x\colon  a = x]]></fr:tex>. We say that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is <fr:em><fr:strong>contractible</fr:strong></fr:em> when it comes equipped with some <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a:A]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is contractible with centre <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex>. We sometimes refer to a contractible type as a <fr:em><fr:strong>singleton</fr:strong></fr:em>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
